WEBVTT

01:59.813 --> 02:03.066
- Lula loves her syrup.
- You have enough syrup.

02:03.149 --> 02:05.819
Mrs. Butterworths
isn't a squirt bottle.

02:05.902 --> 02:07.862
It's no big deal. You've had enough.

02:07.946 --> 02:11.241
- Mom, these aren't brown enough.
- Do you want me to burn them?

02:11.324 --> 02:13.660
No, but I just want them more brown.

02:13.743 --> 02:16.204
Mikey, Mom's not a short order cook.

02:16.287 --> 02:17.789
Eat up now.

02:19.416 --> 02:22.085
Double knots?
We never did double knots.

02:22.168 --> 02:25.130
- Sweetie, I can't get it.
- Don't use a fork.

02:25.171 --> 02:27.882
No bubbles at the table.
Eat your breakfast first.

02:27.966 --> 02:30.844
She's right, you know,
my eggs taste like bubbles now.

02:36.641 --> 02:39.686
- Hurry up, honey, you'll be late.
- All right.

02:39.769 --> 02:43.189
The van needs an inspection sticker.
Good luck.

02:48.069 --> 02:50.238
Alrighty.

02:50.321 --> 02:52.866
What's this?
Look who's hiding.

02:52.949 --> 02:57.370
Mr. Dino...
and another weird stowaway.

02:57.454 --> 02:59.539
Okay, Nathan, no cereal in my thingie.

02:59.622 --> 03:01.374
- Bye, sweetheart.
- Bye, honey.

03:01.416 --> 03:02.625
Nathan!

03:36.576 --> 03:38.745
- What's that?
- What?

03:38.828 --> 03:39.996
That.

03:41.664 --> 03:43.625
Maple syrup.

03:47.087 --> 03:51.466
Mmm, man! Can you believe
that comes from a tree?

03:51.549 --> 03:53.259
Don't taste my pants.

03:53.301 --> 03:55.095
I can't taste your pants?

03:55.136 --> 03:56.930
Ever.

03:56.971 --> 03:58.264
- Ever?
- No.

03:58.348 --> 04:00.600
Well, don't spill maple syrup on them.

04:00.683 --> 04:03.436
Just because it's there
doesn't mean you have to taste it.

04:03.478 --> 04:05.563
- I like maple syrup.
- Not from my pants.

04:05.647 --> 04:07.107
I love it.

04:10.151 --> 04:14.239
How about this:
What if you had, like, an inkpad...

04:15.281 --> 04:19.619
only instead of ink,
it was soaked in maple syrup.

04:19.702 --> 04:22.163
Or peppermint.
Any flavor you wanted.

04:23.540 --> 04:29.087
- And you just open up your little pad.
- Right.

04:29.170 --> 04:32.757
And you press your finger on it
and then you taste your finger.

04:32.799 --> 04:37.095
Peppermint. Any time of day.
Or cherry.

04:37.137 --> 04:40.098
Wouldn't the pad get disgusting
after awhile?

04:40.140 --> 04:41.641
Disgusting how?

04:41.724 --> 04:44.644
I don't know. You keep touching it
with your filthy fingers.

04:44.686 --> 04:48.481
Couple of days that flavor pad's like
some mattress you find at the dump.

04:49.274 --> 04:51.651
You're right. It's no good.

04:59.492 --> 05:00.660
Tim.

05:00.744 --> 05:04.247
- Did you get your performance chart?
- Yeah.

05:04.330 --> 05:07.167
Well, look at mine. I don't get it.

05:07.208 --> 05:09.294
Good. Fair. Fair. Good.

05:09.335 --> 05:12.088
Then it falls into the red
in the focus department.

05:12.172 --> 05:15.884
Well, you know, Nick, that's because
you're a dreamer. You know?

05:15.967 --> 05:20.054
- I'm not a dreamer.
- You're not the most focused person.

05:20.138 --> 05:21.723
You're a dreamer.

05:21.806 --> 05:25.143
Yeah. I'm a dreamer?

05:25.185 --> 05:28.062
Hey, you want to feel something?
Come here.

05:28.146 --> 05:30.148
Sit in this chair. Come here.

05:30.231 --> 05:32.192
Okay.

05:32.233 --> 05:33.693
Check this out.

05:36.738 --> 05:37.739
Whoa.

05:37.822 --> 05:40.325
- Sit back.
- Oh, this is some chair!

05:40.408 --> 05:41.826
- Do you like it?
- Yeah.

05:41.868 --> 05:43.411
Feel this.

05:44.287 --> 05:46.247
What is that?

05:46.331 --> 05:48.875
- Lumbar support.
- That is good.

05:48.958 --> 05:53.171
- It's made especially for your spine.
- I like it.

05:53.213 --> 05:56.132
Comes with the office.
And the promotion.

05:56.216 --> 05:59.427
- Right.
- Thinking of buying a swimming pool?

05:59.511 --> 06:01.221
- What, are you kidding?
- I am.

06:01.304 --> 06:04.224
- Thinking bean-shaped.

06:04.307 --> 06:07.727
Expensive. Bean-shaped?

06:10.396 --> 06:12.857
Take a look at my performance chart.

06:12.941 --> 06:16.736
Look at your focus. It's way up there.
It's in the yellow.

06:16.778 --> 06:20.865
I'm telling you, you get your focus
even into the orange, just the orange...

06:20.907 --> 06:23.201
I guarantee you can have
a chair like that.

06:23.243 --> 06:25.120
- Really?
- And an office like this.

06:25.203 --> 06:27.747
And a piano-shaped pool
if that's what you want.

06:27.831 --> 06:30.625
It's all there for you.
All you got to do is focus.

06:30.708 --> 06:32.335
Just work a little bit harder.

06:32.419 --> 06:36.256
You can get bumped up to sandpaper
with me and the world opens up.

06:36.297 --> 06:39.509
You know what, man?
You could really sack out in this thing.

06:39.592 --> 06:42.971
I'm telling you, your numbers
aren't that bad. It's just focus.

06:43.054 --> 06:47.392
If you put together everything else, you
got a really strong thing going on...

06:49.978 --> 06:52.564
Nick. Nick!

06:54.190 --> 06:56.860
- I got to get back to work.
- Yeah.

06:56.943 --> 06:58.778
- Good talk.
- Yeah, good talk.

07:00.238 --> 07:02.073
- Remember what I said.
- Focus.

07:02.115 --> 07:04.451
- Just get into orange.
- That's all I need.

07:04.534 --> 07:06.953
Don't even worry about yellow,
just orange.

07:13.543 --> 07:16.463
Do you ever just watch your hand?

07:16.504 --> 07:17.922
No.

07:17.964 --> 07:20.175
I was just looking at my hand today.

07:21.092 --> 07:24.012
It was like a separate thing.

07:24.095 --> 07:25.346
It was...

07:26.806 --> 07:29.142
