that gets rid of dog turds,

08:26.199 --> 08:29.536
you are home free, my friend.
Home free.

08:45.427 --> 08:46.761
What?

08:46.845 --> 08:48.263
Nothing.

08:49.889 --> 08:52.016
Liposuction.

08:54.853 --> 08:57.147
You mean, where they suck the fat out?

08:57.230 --> 08:59.315
There's a thing about it in here.

08:59.399 --> 09:02.026
You're fine. You don't need
to get fat sucked out.

09:02.068 --> 09:05.405
- If we had a little extra money...
- We don't have extra money.

09:05.447 --> 09:07.782
- We have a little.
- Not to get fat sucked out.

09:11.536 --> 09:12.537
Hello?

09:12.579 --> 09:16.124
- Timmy. Timmy, check this out.
- What?

09:16.207 --> 09:19.085
You know that invention of mine
that makes turds disappear?

09:20.378 --> 09:22.172
I got a name for it.

09:22.255 --> 09:24.299
Vapoorize.

09:24.382 --> 09:28.762
Just like vaporize only you add an "o"
so you got "poo" right in the middle.

09:28.845 --> 09:30.221
Yeah, I get it.

09:30.263 --> 09:33.600
Do you see how perfect it is?
Maybe even underline the poo.

09:33.641 --> 09:35.268
Va-poo-rize.

09:35.351 --> 09:37.270
- All right.
- Vapoorize.

09:37.312 --> 09:38.938
Goodbye.

09:39.022 --> 09:40.774
- Nick?
- Mmm-hmm.

09:40.857 --> 09:43.193
- What did he want?
- Nothing.

09:44.194 --> 09:46.446
Vapoorize.

09:48.782 --> 09:52.118
Next up, ladies
and gentlemen, Nathan Vanderpark.

09:52.202 --> 09:55.789
- Go ahead, Nathan.
- All right.

09:55.872 --> 09:59.167
- Here we go, Nathan. Here we go.

10:01.127 --> 10:02.962
- Almost.
- All right.

10:03.463 --> 10:05.965
- Nice try.
- All right, Nathan, let's...

10:06.007 --> 10:08.384
Close one.

10:08.468 --> 10:11.429
Oh! Come... all right.

10:11.471 --> 10:13.139
That's enough. Hey!

10:13.223 --> 10:15.016
Almost.

10:15.100 --> 10:18.228
- We'll get them next time, no problem.
- Good job.

10:18.311 --> 10:20.355
You know Dimitriov in research?

10:21.439 --> 10:22.732
- Dimitriov?
- Yeah.

10:22.816 --> 10:27.195
- Kind of big beard? Kind of strange?
- No.

10:27.278 --> 10:29.739
- I told him about my invention.
- What invention?

10:29.823 --> 10:31.199
Vapoorize!

10:31.282 --> 10:33.410
Nick, you got a cute name, that's it.

10:33.493 --> 10:36.830
It's not an invention. It's an idea.
It's nothing.

10:36.913 --> 10:39.916
Not according to Dimitriov.
He thinks I'm really on to something.

10:57.100 --> 10:58.977
- Bravo!
- Good stuff.

10:59.018 --> 11:01.187
- Good job.
- Good stuff.

11:01.271 --> 11:05.191
You know what? I love this tent.
There's not one bug.

11:05.233 --> 11:06.568
Guess what?

11:06.651 --> 11:09.279
I went over to Dimitriov's
a couple nights ago.

11:09.362 --> 11:11.322
We ran some experiments in his sink.

11:11.406 --> 11:14.159
- He's having a ball with this thing.
- What thing?

11:14.200 --> 11:16.202
You didn't tell Debbie
about my invention?

11:16.286 --> 11:19.247
No, sorry, I didn't.
Go ahead. This is great.

11:19.330 --> 11:22.000
Check it out.
It's a spray can, okay?

11:22.041 --> 11:24.002
And you spray it on dog poo...

11:24.043 --> 11:26.838
and the poo disappears.

11:26.880 --> 11:31.342
That is an awesome invention.
I mean, we could sure use it.

11:31.384 --> 11:35.388
It's not an invention. It's nothing.
I mean, how does it work?

11:35.472 --> 11:38.975
It's a spray can and you spray it on.

11:39.058 --> 11:41.227
- Exactly.
- Right?

11:41.311 --> 11:43.438
Yeah, I know.
But what makes it disappear?

11:43.521 --> 11:45.231
Things don't just disappear.

11:45.273 --> 11:48.026
I don't know, honey.
How does anything work?

11:48.068 --> 11:51.362
How does electricity work?
I think it's a great idea.

11:51.404 --> 11:53.990
So do l. I think it's really exciting.

11:54.074 --> 11:56.076
- You're nuts.

11:56.159 --> 11:57.577
Dessert, everybody?

11:57.660 --> 12:00.038
- I'm nuts. I'm crazy.
- You're crazy!

12:00.080 --> 12:03.166
Hey, I have an invention.
Honey, I have an invention.

12:03.249 --> 12:07.128
It's this button you press and
you sprout wings and you can fly.

12:07.212 --> 12:10.757
You can fly into outer space,
to the moon, to Jupiter if you like.

12:18.181 --> 12:20.225
He's doing so well.

12:20.266 --> 12:22.435
He's not doing anything.

12:22.519 --> 12:25.980
- Does he have any lines?
- No, honey, he's a tree.

12:26.773 --> 12:29.317
Three months of rehearsal.

12:31.444 --> 12:35.573
Dimitriov wants to know
if I want to take it to the next level.

12:35.615 --> 12:38.743
Four thousand bucks.
You want to go in with me, 50/50?

12:38.827 --> 12:42.497
I pray to God
you're kidding.

12:42.580 --> 12:44.290
- Your invention?
- Yeah.

12:44.374 --> 12:48.461
We've been working with dry ice.
We've got something amazing.

12:48.545 --> 12:49.796
Nick, forget it.

12:49.879 --> 12:54.467
No, wait a minute. $2,000.
We have that in our savings.

12:54.551 --> 12:55.760
Who knows?

12:55.802 --> 12:58.972
Shit doesn't just disappear.

12:59.055 --> 13:00.765
It has to go somewhere.

13:00.807 --> 13:05.770
And it's not an invention, it's an idea.
It's a pie in the sky idea.

13:05.854 --> 13:08.064
And I'll tell you,
as your best friend...

13:08.148 --> 13:11.568
I think you should
just pull out right now.

13:11.651 --> 13:14.446
Don't waste your money.
You're gonna regret it.

13:14.487 --> 13:15.947
"It's pie in the sky."

13:18.366 --> 13:22.036
Where are the kids?
What's happening?

13:22.120 --> 13:23.997
Honey?

13:27.167 --> 13:29.669
I have champagne glasses, too.

13:29.753 --> 13:31.212
All right!

13:31.296 --> 13:32.756
What's happening?

13:32.839 --> 13:36.593
Okay, let me get it for you.
I'll do everything.

13:36.676 --> 13:40.638
You just stay there and just relax
and get ready for the big stuff.

13:40.680 --> 13:43.641
- We got it.

13:43.683 --> 13:45.059
- Exciting.
- Watch this.

13:45.143 --> 13:48.855
I'm so glad you guys are here!
This is Dimitriov.

13:48.938 --> 13:51.691
- Meet our best friends in the universe.
- How do you do?

13:51.733 --> 13:54.527
Give Tim the flash, Big D.

13:54.569 --> 13:56.321
Okay. Here, take it.

13:56.362 --> 13:57.530
Goggles.

13:59.199 --> 14:01.159
Shine it right on her, buddy boy.

14:01.201 --> 14:02.827
"Her"?

14:22.639 --> 14:26.184
- You told me it would work and it did!
- Did you see that?!

14:26.267 --> 14:29.395
It works.
It works like a charm.

14:35.276 --> 14:36.903
Did you guys see that?

14:36.986 --> 14:40.031
Get a camera.
There's nothing to shoot!

14:40.115 --> 14:44.953
Spray some on my butt
because I shat my pants. Yeah!

14:45.036 --> 14:48.832
We are going to be so rich, Dimitriov!

14:48.915 --> 14:51.042
Vapoorize!

14:55.088 --> 14:57.257
God, we are going
to be so rich!

15:02.303 --> 15:04.722
No matter what kind of dog you have,
let's face it,

15:04.764 --> 15:06.641
they all gotta do their "business."

15:06.724 --> 15:08.560
Vapoorize!

15:08.601 --> 15:09.936
That's right!

15:10.019 --> 15:12.772
One spray: Problem solved.

15:12.814 --> 15:14.566
Is this some kind of video trick?

15:14.607 --> 15:15.942
No.

15:15.984 --> 15:18.903
It's the miracle spray.
One spray and doggy doo disappears.

15:18.945 --> 15:21.948
No fuss, no muss, no tools,
no robot arm...

15:22.031 --> 15:24.200
"How do I work it? I don't know!"

15:24.284 --> 15:26.286
- Too good to be true?
- No!

15:26.369 --> 15:28.621
Because life is tough enough.

15:28.663 --> 15:30.331
Now at stores everywhere.

15:30.331 --> 15:30.623
Now at stores everywhere.

16:16.628 --> 16:19.172
Now's a good time
to break the big news.

16:21.216 --> 16:26.179
I have decided to run for Congress.

16:26.262 --> 16:27.680
Congress.

16:29.224 --> 16:31.017
No, I'm serious.

16:31.101 --> 16:35.563
Yeah. I mean, not the big Congress,
of course, the little one.

16:35.647 --> 16:38.525
- "The little one."
- "The little one?"

16:38.608 --> 16:42.445
Yeah. Actually, it might be
the state senate. I can't remember.

16:42.529 --> 16:44.989
Anyway, I'm super excited...

16:45.031 --> 16:47.659
because we are so lucky...

16:47.742 --> 16:51.079
and we have so, so, so much.

16:51.162 --> 16:53.665
And I feel like
we should give something back.

16:53.706 --> 16:56.584
So, I've decided
I'm going to run for Congress

16:56.668 --> 16:58.962
or state senate or whatever.

16:59.045 --> 17:03.049
And my main platform...

17:03.133 --> 17:05.175
is going to be...

17:06.719 --> 17:08.430
the environment.

17:11.182 --> 17:12.851
State senate.

17:12.934 --> 17:15.728
Environment, like the whole environment?

17:15.770 --> 17:20.483
Yeah. I believe in all environments
and I'm going to say it.

17:21.734 --> 17:24.738
And now for dessert.

17:24.820 --> 17:26.865
Flan!

17:26.948 --> 17:29.576
- Flan! Oh, boy!
- Whoo!

17:29.659 --> 17:33.705
- Come on, kids, flan time!
- Get down here, the flan's here!

17:33.788 --> 17:35.790
Flan, kids! Flan!

17:35.874 --> 17:37.459
I love flan. Do you?

17:37.542 --> 17:38.793
What is flan?

17:38.877 --> 17:40.962
My God, you're in for such a treat.

17:41.045 --> 17:44.090
- You don't know flan?
- Eat your flan, buddy. Kids, flan!

17:44.174 --> 17:47.427
- Guys, flan's on the table!
- Flan!

17:47.469 --> 17:48.762
Flan! Flan!

17:48.803 --> 17:52.390
Flan! Yay, flan! Flan!

17:52.474 --> 17:54.267
What's flan?

17:54.350 --> 17:57.145
"Jasper and Amos
shine the flashlight into the hole.

17:57.228 --> 18:01.733
