24:58.858 --> 25:01.361
The pool people
come tomorrow.

25:14.624 --> 25:17.544
Just wait and see this, Dad.

25:20.713 --> 25:22.674
Whoa! You the man.

25:22.757 --> 25:24.551
- You're the man.
- Yeah!

25:58.835 --> 26:00.920
Hey, Timmy, check this out!

26:01.004 --> 26:02.422
Yeah!

26:02.464 --> 26:04.883
Yah! Yah!

26:09.345 --> 26:11.014
Yah!

26:15.310 --> 26:17.437
Mr. Dingman!

26:17.520 --> 26:20.315
Mr. Parmenter wants to see you!
Section 1 1!

26:21.441 --> 26:24.402
You wanted to see me?

26:24.444 --> 26:26.529
You all right?

26:26.613 --> 26:27.655
What?

26:27.739 --> 26:30.033
You seem distracted!

26:30.950 --> 26:32.285
- What?
- Come on!

26:32.368 --> 26:35.413
Your performance chart's
pretty good until here.

26:35.497 --> 26:38.833
And then your focus
nosedives into the red.

26:38.917 --> 26:40.668
You see?

26:40.752 --> 26:45.006
Now, is there anything that happened
around here...

26:46.508 --> 26:49.177
you might like to talk about?

26:49.260 --> 26:50.386
No.

26:50.470 --> 26:52.597
- You sure?
- Yeah. No.

26:53.807 --> 26:55.433
Any reason?

26:55.517 --> 26:57.477
Reason? No, I can't think of...

26:57.519 --> 27:01.189
Any reason at all?

27:01.272 --> 27:06.277
No. No reason. No.
I mean, nothing I can think of.

27:06.361 --> 27:08.238
I mean...

27:08.321 --> 27:12.450
you know, other than every day
I get into my little shit-box car

27:12.534 --> 27:16.121
and there he is,
with the wind in his hair...

27:16.204 --> 27:18.665
on his great big shiny horse.

27:18.748 --> 27:23.294
And I drive off to do what?
To make sandpaper.

27:24.212 --> 27:27.382
To make paper with sand on it.

27:29.592 --> 27:33.555
I'd love to see you try to turn your
weasely little mouth into a fake smile,

27:33.638 --> 27:35.557
day after day after day...

27:35.640 --> 27:38.518
while waving toodly-fucking-do
to your best friend,

27:38.601 --> 27:42.230
who's rearing up on a big white horse
like he's the Lone Ranger.

27:42.313 --> 27:44.816
Then I'd like to see
your performance chart,

27:44.858 --> 27:47.694
you beady-eyed
little shrimp-boat bastard!

27:49.863 --> 27:51.990
Is that a reason?

27:55.702 --> 27:59.038
I mean, is that a reason?

28:19.559 --> 28:21.227
Hi.

28:21.770 --> 28:26.608
I don't really drink,
but my family just left me

28:26.691 --> 28:29.819
and I got fired and I want a drink.

28:29.903 --> 28:35.241
So, if you could just give me whatever
you'd have if you wanted to drink.

28:36.576 --> 28:37.952
Please.

28:43.291 --> 28:44.751
Harsh.

28:47.754 --> 28:49.422
Abandoned.

28:49.756 --> 28:51.841
Fired.

28:53.927 --> 28:56.262
It's harsh, man.

28:59.432 --> 29:03.103
Know what the best job
I ever got fired from was?

29:06.606 --> 29:08.942
Pretzel kiosk.

29:08.983 --> 29:12.862
Afternoon shift. Just loved it,
don't know why, just did.

29:12.946 --> 29:15.281
Could be the apron, who the hell knows?

29:15.365 --> 29:18.493
Or maybe the feeling of power you get
when there's a crowd.

29:18.576 --> 29:21.121
One hand rolls dough,
ties those babies off.

29:21.204 --> 29:26.459
The other hand maybe works the soda,
refills the mustard. It's quite a thing.

29:26.543 --> 29:28.086
I'll tell you a secret.

29:28.169 --> 29:31.506
If a pretzel is a quality pretzel,
you don't need salt.

29:31.589 --> 29:33.258
It's just a fact.

29:40.014 --> 29:41.433
How come?

29:42.225 --> 29:45.353
Your family up
and blew out of town on you?

29:46.813 --> 29:50.066
Thank you, but I don't really feel like
talking about it right now.

29:50.150 --> 29:52.777
- Thank you.
- Okay.

29:52.819 --> 29:55.572
So, how come you got canned?

29:57.240 --> 29:59.909
It's a whole different topic.

30:01.077 --> 30:02.996
I just blew up.

30:04.080 --> 30:07.500
Good for you, man. Good for you.
Good for you.

30:08.334 --> 30:11.171
- Who at?
- I blew up at my boss.

30:11.212 --> 30:13.923
Right on, brother. I hear you.

30:14.007 --> 30:16.426
Man, I hear you!

30:16.509 --> 30:19.679
What'd you go and blow up
at your boss for?

30:20.346 --> 30:25.310
You know, it's like
a long, complicated story.

30:25.351 --> 30:29.522
Well, that is sensational.
I'm the J-Man, by the way.

30:30.815 --> 30:32.317
- Tim.
- Tim.

30:32.358 --> 30:34.027
Ike.

30:34.110 --> 30:36.029
Another round, please.

30:36.071 --> 30:39.324
Something fruity
for me and my friend, Tim.

30:39.365 --> 30:41.326
On the J-Man.

30:42.410 --> 30:44.370
Okay, Tim...

30:44.871 --> 30:48.708
just let it tumble out
like circus freaks, man.

30:48.750 --> 30:50.460
I'm here for you.

30:50.543 --> 30:53.254
The J-Man is zeroed in, okay?

30:54.130 --> 30:55.673
Go.

30:57.550 --> 30:59.636
Go.

30:59.719 --> 31:03.515
Well, I have this friend.
He's my best friend.

31:03.556 --> 31:06.267
I love the guy.
I mean, it's like we're, you know...

31:06.351 --> 31:09.354
Our families do everything together.

31:09.395 --> 31:12.565
- Used to go to work together every day.
- Keep it coming.

31:12.649 --> 31:15.110
And he'd have these stupid...

31:15.193 --> 31:17.570
He'd have these stupid ideas.

31:17.612 --> 31:19.697
Open your heart. Open your heart.

31:19.781 --> 31:22.033
Where does it come from?

31:22.075 --> 31:23.701
Shit.

31:23.743 --> 31:25.370
It's all from shit.

31:25.453 --> 31:28.415
You know who you are?
You're like that guy...

31:28.498 --> 31:30.750
Che, Che something.

31:30.834 --> 31:35.004
- "Che something"?
- Up with the people. People power.

31:35.088 --> 31:38.174
Or the kid that stole a chicken
with the golden eggs.

31:38.258 --> 31:39.884
What a fantastic chicken.

31:39.926 --> 31:43.096
Who's for the giant? Nobody.
You hear what I'm saying.

31:43.179 --> 31:44.722
You're the hero.

31:44.806 --> 31:47.100
Forget Che! You're like Robin Hood.

31:47.183 --> 31:49.477
- Robin Hood? Really?
- Listen to me.

31:49.561 --> 31:53.148
Listen to me. Life's unfair.
It's a raw deal planet, Jack.

31:53.231 --> 31:55.900
You, my little dumbbell friend,
are Mr. Everyman

31:55.942 --> 32:00.071
and you don't even know it, which makes
you like the grand turbo Mr. Everyman.

32:00.155 --> 32:01.531
Honestly?

32:01.614 --> 32:02.907
Come on.

32:02.949 --> 32:06.077
You're like a great big dimwit.
You know that. Fantastic.

32:06.161 --> 32:07.662
Everyman Dimwit.

32:07.746 --> 32:11.416
That stinking family across the street.
Who wouldn't feel like you?

32:14.085 --> 32:17.130
I like you.
I'm glad I came in here.

32:17.213 --> 32:18.631
You know that?

32:18.673 --> 32:22.302
Ringlets! Give me a break.
Let me tell you a little story.

32:22.385 --> 32:23.928
When I was maybe 1 0,

32:24.012 --> 32:28.558
there was this kid across the street,
Ernie "Nice Kid."

32:28.641 --> 32:32.771
Ernie had everything.
Only kid around with a BB gun, okay?

32:32.812 --> 32:35.857
So one night I see
the whole family drive off.

32:35.940 --> 32:40.195
What'd I do? I sneak across the street
and find the BB gun.

32:40.278 --> 32:44.741
I squeeze off maybe five, ten pot shots
at the windows...

32:44.824 --> 32:46.659
Hello. In my house.

32:46.701 --> 32:49.954
- In your house?
- Yes, you got...

32:49.996 --> 32:51.831
You squoze off to your house?

32:51.873 --> 32:54.334
You got it.
Next morning my old man gets up,

32:54.417 --> 32:58.129
sees all these little BB holes
in our windows.

32:58.171 --> 33:01.466
He marches across the street,
bangs on the door and Tim,

33:01.508 --> 33:03.426
my little bozo friend,

33:03.510 --> 33:07.847
things changed big time
over there in Ernieville.

33:12.519 --> 33:15.355
That's what you got to do!

33:15.438 --> 33:17.482
- What?
- Shake things up.

33:17.524 --> 33:19.567
Over there, man.
Shake them up.

33:19.651 --> 33:24.364
Make them think of something besides
the temperature in that candy-ass pool.

33:26.741 --> 33:30.203
- Shit, what time is it?
- What kind of question is that?

33:31.162 --> 33:34.124
I got to get back!
They can't build the pool!

33:34.958 --> 33:37.335
Ike, cab...

33:37.377 --> 33:39.504
on the J-Man.

33:39.546 --> 33:43.216
- Come on!

33:50.014 --> 33:51.015
Excuse me!

33:54.644 --> 33:56.062
Sir! Sir!

33:56.104 --> 33:57.689
You have to stop, please.

33:57.730 --> 33:59.441
Here they come!

33:59.524 --> 34:01.401
- Whoo!
- Hi, Mom!

34:01.484 --> 34:03.695
Digging, no. We can't pay for the pool.

34:03.737 --> 34:06.239
We don't... we can't pay for the pool.

34:06.281 --> 34:08.699
No, no. Stop! Sir!
No mas!

34:08.742 --> 34:11.703
- Sir, I'll talk to the office.

34:12.203 --> 34:14.038
Good afternoon, Mr. Tim.

34:14.080 --> 34:18.460
- Hi.
- You look really, really wonderful.

34:18.543 --> 34:22.213
And here is something from
your great friends across the street

34:22.255 --> 34:24.924
while your wonderful family is away.

34:33.766 --> 34:37.478
"Thought you might enjoy a taste
from our newly acquired vineyard."

35:01.002 --> 35:05.882
You got to shake things up.
Over there, man. Shake them up.

35:13.098 --> 35:15.183
Carousel of dreams.

35:17.310 --> 35:19.479
Casa Corky.

35:20.522 --> 35:22.273
Casa Corky.

35:25.693 --> 35:27.487
Incredible.

35:27.529 --> 35:29.239
Incredible hedge work.

35:36.621 --> 35:38.623
You got to shake things up.

35:38.706 --> 35:40.834
Over there, man.
Shake them up.

35:40.917 --> 35:44.462
Shake things up.
Shake them up.

36:07.193 --> 36:08.820
Huh?

36:26.045 --> 36:27.088
Corky.

36:28.840 --> 36:31.009
My God. How is this possible?

36:31.050 --> 36:33.762
How could a little arrow
kill a big horse?

36:33.845 --> 36:36.139
Come on, Corky.
Corky, come on, come on.

36:36.222 --> 36:39.309
It's just a little arrow.
Come on, Corky.

36:39.392 --> 36:40.810
Giddy up, boy.

36:40.894 --> 36:43.021
Corky. Giddy up. Giddy up.

36:43.104 --> 36:45.064
Corky.

36:47.108 --> 36:49.277
Okay, Corky.

36:50.278 --> 36:52.572
Come on, boy. One, two.

36:52.614 --> 36:54.657
Come on.

36:54.741 --> 36:56.367
Shit.

36:56.451 --> 36:58.953
Shit. God.

37:00.955 --> 37:03.458
Come on, Corky.

38:01.474 --> 38:03.101
Hey.

38:06.729 --> 38:08.982
Cock-a-doodle-doo.

38:09.065 --> 38:12.193
Car return.
How's that for service?

38:12.277 --> 38:16.573
I'd probably still be driving a limo
if it wasn't for the hat.

38:16.656 --> 38:17.657
Hats.

38:17.741 --> 38:20.118
Hats make my head itch.

38:20.160 --> 38:23.288
- What time is it?
- You got a time hang-up, don't you?

38:23.329 --> 38:24.831
Oh, God.

38:24.914 --> 38:27.459
- Look at me.
- I was thinking the same thing.

38:27.500 --> 38:29.377
You are one big stinking pig, Tim.

38:29.461 --> 38:31.129
- How'd you get my keys?
- Keys?

38:31.171 --> 38:34.632
The J-Man don't usually need keys,
my little dumbbell pal.

38:34.674 --> 38:38.720
So, that's the place?

38:38.803 --> 38:42.515
Look at it. All from shit?
I see what you mean.

38:42.599 --> 38:46.060
I don't even live here and that place
is pulling my testicles up.

38:46.144 --> 38:48.980
I mean, literally,
they're actually coming up.

38:49.022 --> 38:51.149
You ever get that?

38:51.191 --> 38:52.692
I killed his horse.

38:52.734 --> 38:55.403
- What?
- I killed his horse.

38:55.487 --> 38:58.448
That story you were telling
about shaking things up...

38:58.531 --> 39:00.992
I went over there and
I shot this bow and arrow,

39:01.034 --> 39:04.579
and I shot at my house
and I hit his horse.

39:04.662 --> 39:06.372
He was eating apples in my yard.

39:06.456 --> 39:10.293
There was a hole because we were going
to have a pool and I buried him in it.

39:10.376 --> 39:13.671
- Well, now.
- Daddy! We're home!

39:13.713 --> 39:15.090
No!

39:19.719 --> 39:21.179
It's my family.

39:21.221 --> 39:22.514
- Hide!
- Hide?

39:22.555 --> 39:24.432
Hide! Hide.

39:24.516 --> 39:28.228
- Hide? Can't I just mosey off?
- No! Don't mosey off.

39:28.311 --> 39:30.688
No, you can't mosey off.
They'll see you!

39:30.730 --> 39:33.066
- So?
- So? So, what are you doing here?

39:33.108 --> 39:35.193
Who are you?
You're some guy from a bar.

39:35.276 --> 39:39.447
What's wrong with...?
I'm the J-Man, bringing your car back.

39:39.531 --> 39:41.032
Daddy!

39:41.074 --> 39:42.951
- Hey, tiger!
- Daddy!

39:43.034 --> 39:46.329
- Hey, peanut.
- We all really missed you.

39:46.413 --> 39:49.958
You look terrible.
Honey, one question.

39:50.041 --> 39:53.169
What is at the heart of everything?
What I'm asking you is:

39:53.253 --> 39:56.589
What is at the heart of the heart
of the heart of the heart?

39:56.673 --> 39:59.717
Do you know what the answer is?
Self-love.

39:59.759 --> 40:02.971
Windsong told me that I have been
hating myself for resenting you.

40:03.054 --> 40:06.808
And you've been resenting yourself
for passing up on a big opportunity.

40:06.891 --> 40:10.228
What we need to do
is we need to focus on what we have.

40:11.855 --> 40:14.566
Hey! Oh, hey!

40:14.649 --> 40:16.943
This is... This guy...

40:16.985 --> 40:18.737
Honey...

40:18.778 --> 40:22.365
this is...
This man is the man...

40:23.533 --> 40:26.035
who was in the bathroom.
I didn't tell you.

40:30.206 --> 40:34.586
Honey... something happened
while you were gone, something bad.

40:34.627 --> 40:36.129
What?

40:36.171 --> 40:37.797
I'll take it from here, Tim.

40:39.299 --> 40:41.259
Mrs. Dingman...

40:41.301 --> 40:44.012
I'm Elmo Carp, pool rep.

40:44.095 --> 40:48.850
Your husband and I were up here
discussing your swimming pool options.

40:48.933 --> 40:50.810
- Swimming pool options?
- Yes.

40:50.894 --> 40:52.937
You see, we dug it,
we had to fill it back in.

40:52.979 --> 40:56.524
We're sorry as heck.
Where do we go from here?

40:56.608 --> 40:59.444
That's the point we were at
when you barged in.

40:59.486 --> 41:02.405
I don't understand.
Fill it back in?

41:02.489 --> 41:05.700
So you mean we're not getting a pool?

41:05.784 --> 41:08.995
No, sonny boy, I'm afraid not.
Too many gosh darn pipes.

41:09.079 --> 41:10.455
- Pipes?
- Yes.

41:10.497 --> 41:12.749
Underground pipes in your yard,

41:12.832 --> 41:17.921
but I've intruded enough
on your little family reunion here.

41:18.004 --> 41:19.714
I'll be on my way.

41:19.798 --> 41:22.675
And thanks for filthying up
your clothes,

41:22.717 --> 41:24.677
helping me fill in the big hole, Tim.

41:24.719 --> 41:27.972
Ma'am, your husband's
got the back of a coal miner.

41:28.014 --> 41:31.476
I know because I've mined coal.
See you.

41:39.984 --> 41:42.070
Something's happened to Corky.

41:42.153 --> 41:43.780
- What?
- Corky?

41:43.863 --> 41:46.324
- Have you seen Corky?
- I haven't seen Corky.

41:46.366 --> 41:48.243
- Corky's gone?
- Have you seen Corky?

41:48.326 --> 41:50.328
- I have not seen Corky.
- That's what I mean.

41:50.412 --> 41:52.914
We've been looking and looking.
Where could he be?

41:52.997 --> 41:56.501
- A great big horse, where?
- Nick, a horse can't just disappear.

